  "tables": [
    {
      "block_id": "3364750c-f3ba-80aa-b32d-e43f3fbb27c4",
      "heading": "Abstract",
      "rows": [
        [
          "Context",
          "Teaching Method",
          "Recommender System Type",
          "Target of Recommendation",
          "Students",
          "Courses",
          "Data sources",
          "Initialization Method",
          "Updates to Recommendations",
          "Preprocessing Details",
          "Recommendation types",
          "Evaluation",
          "Comments",
          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "MOOC",
          "Mobile E-Learning",
          "Outcome-Based Educational Recommender System (OBER); method-agnostic framework with Fixed trajectory, Collaborative Filtering (CF), and Knowledge-Based (KB) filtering",
          "Learning items / next items in a learning trajectory to maximize mastery of outcomes",
          "Over 5,700 learners total; experiment groups: CF 1856, Fixed 1963, KB 1932",
          "NamazApp learning content",
          "Learner profiles, learning items, interaction logs, outcome tree, item–outcome alignment mappings, mastery scores",
          "Learning outcomes first established with domain experts; outcomes aligned to items; in NamazApp, an LLM produced initial item–outcome alignments, later checked and edited by the team; mastery computed from best result on verifying items",
          "Recommendations delivered during normal app usage; framework supports swapping recommendation methods without changing logging or mastery calculation",
          "Minimal entity-relation schema with Learner–Item–Outcome entities; item-outcome alignments labeled as promotes or verifies; mastery formula uses learner’s best result on items verifying each outcome; total mastery is sum over outcomes",
          "Personalized next-item recommendations / learning trajectories",
          "Two-week randomized split test comparing Fixed, CF, and KB. Metrics: Retention, Relevance (CTR), and Mastery. Results: CF had highest retention (6.16) and relevance (0.3033), but Fixed achieved highest mastery (0.4641), followed by KB (0.4212) and CF (0.3899)",
          "Links recommendation directly to learning outcomes rather than only engagement. Contribution is mainly methodological: adding outcomes and assessment into the RS schema so different methods can be compared on pedagogical impact. The page-3 schema and page-6 evaluation flow make the framework especially clear",
          "Findings are specific to NamazApp and non-formal learning; larger/longer experiments needed for stronger significance claims; generalizability to other educational contexts remains open"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
  ],
