    {
      "id": "3364750c-f3ba-804f-8c2f-fe14ef3d6dd5",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Most ERS suffer from the problem of being evaluated with pedagogically unmeaningful metrics. Authors introduce OBER which introduces outcomes and assessments into the schema → allowing the evaluation of learning gains. \n\nAuthors A/B/C tested their framework on a set of 5700 students over 2 weeks using 3 methods - Fixed, CF and KB. Fixed path maximized mastery, while CF maximized retention. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "3364750c-f3ba-804f-8c2f-fe14ef3d6dd5",
        "parent": {
